						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">ChōḻaRājakēsarivarmaṉ, Year 3 = c. 9th Century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records an endowment of 70 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold left in charge of the <hi rend="italic">mūlapaṟaḍai</hi> of Thiruveḷḷaṟai by Chāttuvāy Kāñjan Dāmōdiran of the same village, for feeding a Brahmana versed in the Vedas, every noon after offering is made in the temple of Tiruvānaikkal Perumānaḍigaḷ.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> Vol. XIII, No. 27.]</p>						

						</summary>
